10:
Look at all these decorations...
They're from Yamato, aren't they?
17:
Please. It comes with the job. I've
learned so much about different
cultures!
20:
Oh, and a very happy New Year's to
you too!
23:
What are you doing, Alk? This just
screams "otherworldly tradition."
27:
It's called "kakizome." Think of it as...
a kind of New Year's calligraphy.
Want to give it a try?
31:
Do I? My whole life's about paper
and ink. I'm all over it!
35:
Wow. You really got into calligraphy,
huh?
38:
Yep! And I figured I better look the
part. Feast your eyes on this robe!
And this brush!
40:
Had them custom-made in Yamato.
How do I look?
48:
I've been writing practically my
whole life, but who knew lettering
could be such an art?
49:
I HAVE to spread the word about
this. As a reporter, it's my job to
deliver the best of the world to the
public's front doorstep!
52: Truly, you do your profession proud.
55: Is there any way we can help?
58:
Glad you asked. So first, we've got to
get people interested... And the best
way to do that? Host an event!
63:
I see... A kakizome competition,
where the state of your mind is
reflected in the shape of your
strokes...
66:
Wait, there's prize money?! Like
actual money for writing a single
word?!
72:
You bet! Editing department's
already cleared the whole shebang.
73:
By the way, we're including ink and a
brush with each issue of this
month's Oculus. So all that's left is to
advertise the competition!
76:
I see. We could pass out these
notices, but it may be more efficient
to post them...
79:
What about the shops in Palpebra? I
bet you'd get a lot of eyes there.
83: Alk, you're a genius! Let's move out!
96:
Your strokes are too heavy. Why
don't you try again?
101: I would like to test my hand as well.
103:
It may be difficult in this form, but
the new year is a time for new
challenges.
109:
Phew! Done!
Hey, what do you think?! Not half
bad, if I do say so myself.
111:
I'm a scrivener by trade, by I've
never PAINTED my words before.
There's something... captivating
about it.
113:
Wow, this is great! Good, strong
lettering. After it dries, you should
definitely submit it!
116:
Yeah, why not?
Hey... I've got an idea. We should
frame these! You could even call it
art!
119:
Everyone's really getting into it. I'd
call Operation Kakizome a success.
122:
Hehe. I just love looking at all their
happy faces.
125:
What do you say we submit our own
pieces for the competition?
128:
Sounds like a plan.
Ooh, I'm so excited to see what
everyone wrote!
